{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 216938, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "40815", "body": "According to Blizzard, they made the last cinematic in TFT a realtime 3d animation rather than a prerendered cinematic because they were pressed for time. They would have made it clearer that Arthas did NOT kill Illidan had they not had this constraint.\n\nMaiev Shadowsong's survival may well have been a retcon though, besides the fact that there was an altar of elders rezzing her every so often.\n\nAs for the Black Citadel being renamed the Black Temple and getting moved from HFP to SMV...there's no explanation for that one, really.", "date": "2008-01-11T19:15:52-06:00", "rating": 55, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Blizzard? Pressed for time!", "creationdate": "2008-10-04T11:54:06-05:00", "id": 352955, "rating": 2, "commentid": 216938, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sunderhorse", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Black Citadel was moved from HFP to SMV because it got too messy with this many instances and raids at Hellfire Citadel. Changing the name... well I guess it just fits the better.", "creationdate": "2009-09-01T11:04:28-05:00", "id": 119697, "rating": 19, "commentid": 216938, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Random0028", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-01-11T19:24:43-06:00", 1, "40815"]}
