{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 275247, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Anthara", "body": "A mage can successfully tank in lieu of a Warlock tank. Additional healing may be required. In our case, we added a Tree who kept HoTs on me as well as the raid.\n\nBenefits of a fire mage vs. traditional lock tanks include:\n[ul]\n[li]Reduced risk of [url=?spell=40932]Agonizing Flames[/url] due to [url=?spell=45438]Ice Block[/url][/li]\n[li]Safe management of [url=?spell=41917]Parasites[/url] at the tank spot[/li]\n[li][url=?spell=27128]Fire Ward[/url] to mitigate some [url=?spell=41131]Flame Burst[/url] damage[/li]\n[li]Increased range (41 yds) for safe, continuous threat generation while tanking[/li]\n[li]Increased mobility from [url=?spell=1953]Blink[/url] for faster repositioning[/li]\n[li][url=?spell=38697]Frostbolts[/url] (-40% movement) regardless of spec to help slow nearby [url=?npc=23375]Shadow Demons[/url] as needed[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nOf course, the added healing from [url=?spell=28189]Fel Armor[/url] and generally higher health likely trumps all of the above if you're lucky enough to have a Warlock capable of tanking him. Indirect benefits of having a fire mage tank instead of lock include:\n[ul]\n[li]Allowing every lock to spec [url=?spell=30302]Nether Protection[/url] which is beneficial in many fights (M'uru, Twins, Brutallus, Kalecgos, Illidan, Council, Shahraz, Gorefiend, Supremus, Archimonde, Azgalor, Kaz'rogal) until reaching Alythess, at which point a lock tank is highly preferred and will have to spec out of NP[/li]\n[li]Allowing the lock who would have had to tank to dps instead, pumping out far greater dps (especially during phase 2, the most critical phase) than the fire mage possibly could[/li]\n[li]More distant positioning of Illidan by the melee tank to increase the distance Shadow Demons will have to travel[/li]\n[li][/li]\n[/ul]", "date": "2008-04-21T10:32:38-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-08-05T16:51:26-05:00", 1, "Anthara"]}
