{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 323549, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "BujuArena", "body": "Make VERY SURE that your demon phase tank, if he's a warlock, does not spec [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=30302]Nether Protection[/url]!!!  If he does, and Nether Protection procs, your raid is VERY likely to wipe.  Illidan will stop targeting the warlock tank and shadow blast the next on threat, which is a HUGE problem.\n\nMy guild just wiped on Illidan attempts for a month until we figured out that it wasn't people pulling aggro on the demon phase that was wiping us.  If your guild is dying in phase 4 constantly, this may be the problem.  The solution, of course, is to get your warlock to spec out of Nether Protection.", "date": "2008-07-09T23:33:27-05:00", "rating": 42, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Once the pre-WLK patch goes live, the redesigned [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?spell=30302]Nether Protection[/url] will become a MUST HAVE for Warlock tanking instead of a no-no. Removal of the old immunity mechanic allows NPCs to stick to the caster, while he benefits from high mitigation from that school of magic. Note that it will effect ANY magic school, not just Shadow or Fire.", "creationdate": "2008-09-22T06:51:31-05:00", "id": 47597, "rating": 19, "commentid": 323549, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Anthara", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This was correct with the old nether protection (immunity to shadow and fire).  With the recent change, however, you do not become completely immune to the damage, so he still targets and shoots at you.", "creationdate": "2008-10-16T03:40:02-05:00", "id": 354840, "rating": 2, "commentid": 323549, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "134238", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "No longer nessecary. Nether Protection is no longer immunity (now a 60% reduction, but works for all schools and is 8sec.), and a warlock-tanked mob will continue to attack the warlock when it procs.", "creationdate": "2008-10-29T20:45:43-05:00", "id": 357541, "rating": 2, "commentid": 323549, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "136555", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-07-10T15:59:41-05:00", 1, "BujuArena"]}
