{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 364778, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "176096", "body": "[b]Allegiance with demons [/b]\r\n\r\nAfter the Legion's defeat, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan[/url] was visited by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=25315]Kil'jaeden[/url], who, while noting[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22917] Illidan's[/url] sketchy track record with the Legion, offered him one final chance to serve them. He told him to seek out the [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Frozen_Throne]Frozen Throne[/url], and destroy it. [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Ner%27zhul]Ner'zhul[/url] had grown far too powerful for [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=25315]Kil'jaeden[/url] to control, and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan[/url] was to remove him from the equation; in exchange for more power and magic than he could dream of. He granted him the [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Orb_of_Kil%27jaeden]Orb of Kil'jaeden[/url] to aid him in this task.\r\n\r\nBy harnessing [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32483]Gul'dan's enchanted skull[/url], [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan[/url] came to possess the warlock's memories, and a plan came to mind, but he would need allies to help him. He decided to enlist the aid of old friends.\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan[/url] called the naga to the surface. The naga, formerly the [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Quel%27dorei]Quel'dorei[/url] servitors of [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Queen_Azshara]Azshara[/url], were eager to take vengeance upon the night elves and the other land walking races that had been spared from The Great Sundering. Azshara sent her handmaiden, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=21212]Lady Vashj[/url], to establish contact and she eventually came to lead those who would be known as \"[url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan's[/url] naga.\" But Illidan still had the troublesome warden, [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Maiev_Shadowsong]Maiev Shadowsong[/url], to deal with, as she had persistently chased him all over Kalimdor. [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan[/url] ran to the port of Nendis with his naga and satyr minions cleaning up behind him. When they came to the port, [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan[/url] hijacked a boat and set sail, while a cadre of naga stayed behind to scuttle the ships and ruin all hopes of following him.\r\n\r\nWith the naga swimming in his wake, [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan[/url] came ashore on the Broken Isles \u2014 the ruined remains of Suramar (ironically, the same city where Illidan grew up) which [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Gul%27dan]Gul'dan[/url] and his warlocks had raised twenty years before, and the home of the [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Tomb_of_Sargeras]Tomb of Sargeras[/url].", "date": "2008-08-29T14:04:24-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 366356, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "mythology", "body": "My guild recently got him down for the first time, with entire raid wiped as he died  - but we were still able to loot.\n\nYou are likely to make progress once you continually get him past phase 2 which is probably the hardest phase and requires good tanking. \n\nPhase 3, 4 & 5 are all very similar, you just need to spread out and stay focused. The main focus needs to be on getting the shadow fiends down, you can nuke in non demon form fairly safely.\n\nA good tanking guide for phase 2 is here: http://www.warcraftmovies.com/stream.php?id=49571&stream=&h=fad1ff2753e92813e0c054634e2cad97", "date": "2008-08-31T20:49:22-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-08-31T20:57:12-05:00", 2, "mythology"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 67, "id": 368312, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "119096", "body": "Illidan, brother of Malfurion Stormrage archdruid and currently battling whatever force is corrupting the Emerald Dream was first corrupted in the first war against the Legion, not by demons but his own resentment and his lust for power. After traveling to Azshara's palace and speaking with Sargeras, he was given 'infinite access' to the Well of Eternity through the tattoo's on his body. His second gift was the fire he was given in place of his eyes which allowed him to see magical energy flowing around him and in others. \n\nTurning several times during the war and saved only by his brother Malfurion, he acquired 12 Vials of Eternity. The vials were part of the Well of Eternity, which was a font of pure magic. At the end of the war at the summit of mount Hyjal he poured most of the vials into the pool at the top and Malfurion found him before Illidan had completed transforming the well. Illidan thought he would be proclaimed a hero, but instead was imprisoned by his brother. To hide the new Well's immense power they planted a seed of the world tree and the dragons blessed the Sin'dorei so that this would never happen again.\n\nIn warcraft III Tyrande loosed Illidan hoping he would aid them in the fight against the legion. Shortly after his release he was contacted by Arthas to slay the Dreadlord Tichondrius. Upon slaying the dreadlord Illidan went for the Skull of Guldan. Not much is known about this artifact, be it the warlock's skull or an artifact of his creation, either way it contained his memories and upon drawing   on its powers it transformed Illidan into his current visage... Malfurion upon discovering the demons in fact did have a hold over him, though Illidan swore otherwise, banished him.\n\nIn WCIII: TFT Illidan was called on by his brother to save both of their love... Tyrande who was captured by the scourge. All the while being sought by Maeiv to return Illidan to imprisonment or to slay him... Illidan tasked with destroying the Lich King by Kil'Jadean sought the Eye of Sargeras, a powerful artifact rumored to be part of the Lord of the Burning Legion, and Titan, he was. A desperate struggle, in the end Arthas threw down Illidan in victory and claimed the armor of the Lich King thus fusing the two souls into one...\n\nIn outland Illidan seeking to find a way that Kil'Jadean would not slay him for his failures, trekked across outland and in the end came to the Black Citadel where Magtheridon ruled Outland with an iron fist. Upon defeating Magtheridon he gave him to the Fel Orcs to win their trust where he now resides in the Hellfire Citadel. Upon receiving news of Illidans actions Kil'Jadean confronted him and after warning him of another failure he would be slain, left him to rule Outland bringing us to the present...", "date": "2008-09-03T15:37:06-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-09-03T15:37:42-05:00", 1, "119096"]}
