{"commentv2": 1, "number": 89, "id": 528430, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "258919", "body": "Illidan is one of the major 3 bosses in the Burning Crusade expansion, alongside Kael'thas and Kil'jaeden. Despite the fact that the trailer for the xpac revolves mostly around him, and the game mostly around his realm (Outland), Illidan is not the final boss of the Burning Crusade. Rather, Kil'jaeden is. \r\n\r\nHe is the Lord of the Outland after he defeated Magtheridon (who is now imprisoned in Hellfire Citadel). He resides in the Black Temple, a former Draenei worship site, with the title \"Betrayer\". Though he is not the hardest boss in the game by any means, defeating him is a worthy feat.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, with the release of Wrath of the Lich King, his rare drops have dropped greatly in value.", "date": "2008-12-24T13:22:56-06:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "There isn't even much focus on Illidan in BC. Hell, you hear more about Kil'jaedan than him.  It's like the movie \"Diary of a Mad Black Woman\": The trailers and previews and *!@# all look like it focuses on one thing (BC: Illidan; movie: that mad (as in \"crazy\") elderly black woman), but that thing barely even shows up in the final product (Illidan isn't the big villain; the movie's actually about some black woman who's mad (as in \"&*!@ed\") at her husband).  Only one thing to say about Blizzard cutting Illidan out of the majority of BC content: EPIC FAIL!", "creationdate": "2009-01-17T08:35:36-06:00", "id": 381190, "rating": 1, "commentid": 528430, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "146819", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 90, "id": 530066, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "81613", "body": "i killed Illidan today and he is at lvl 80 a totally joke.. Phase 2 burn the to fire ones he spown.\r\n\r\nSTAY ALIVE THAT PHASE BLOW ALL CD AND MAX DPS AFTER PHASE 2.\r\n\r\nHe will NOT go on Phase 3 if you burn him really fast!\r\n\r\nGood luck and happy x-mas!\r\n\r\nEpinikion, of Reunion.\r\n\r\nP.S. The raid was a 100% pugged from /trade", "date": "2008-12-25T15:32:22-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 91, "id": 546570, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Psyblade1st", "body": "[quote]Illidan got addicted to the arcane magic and when Azshara started to allie with Sargaras; Enemy of all life\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nIllidan was never addicted, he was simply obsessed about proving it superior to druidic magic.\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote], Malfurion and Tyrande wanted to destroy it with the help of every demigod they know.. Illidan, that was addiced could not left them destroy the Well of Eternity, so he warned Azshara, which nearly cost Tyrande her life.[/quote]\r\n\r\nHe warned Azshara, only to get close enough to destroy the Well himself. But Sargaras figured him out, and burned out his eyes, thinking that this gift/small punishment will employ Illidan against his people.\r\n[quote]\r\nFor that he was called Betrayer and was locked away for 10.000 years to Tyrande released him and set him loose in the world again.. [/quote]\r\n\r\nHe was called the Betrayer for recreating the Well of Eternity in Hyjal summit, a 'gift' to the Night Elves, but Malfurion got furious, and with Cenarious's help, he imprisoned Illidan, and gave Meiev the Wardens power.\r\n\r\n[quote]There he gets the Skull of Guldan.. Story dont tell if it was Guldans skull or an artifact made by him, but it contains a lot of his memories.. it also cost him his soul and he gets \"neither demon nor nightelf, but something more.\"[/quote]\r\n\r\nHe did not make it, but it is most likely Gul'Dan's skull itself, but how it got to the Legion's grasp, while it was surly at Sargaras's tomb is unknown.\r\n\r\nIllidan never 'lost his soul', he simply changed physically, but he never enraged and destroyed everything, he was like he always was.", "date": "2009-01-04T15:08:30-06:00", "rating": 104, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
