{"commentv2": 1, "number": 115, "id": 750385, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "393910", "body": "I liked this character. Think he'll be back? Or do you think he's gone forever? It's easy enough to bring characters back/fake deaths in fantasy games--think Illidan has more potential for growth? \r\n\r\nYou are not prepared.", "date": "2009-06-18T13:25:42-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Don't look so smug! I know what you're thinking, but the Black Temple was merely a setback. Did you honestly believe that I would trust the future to some red, hulking, Eredar mongrel? Hahahaha... Oh no, no, no. He was merely an instrument, a stepping stone to a much larger plan! It has all led to this...and this time, you are not prepared!", "creationdate": "2010-01-24T10:49:33-06:00", "id": 439707, "rating": 0, "commentid": 750385, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "450872", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 116, "id": 761315, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "mrbungle54", "body": "I was thinking the other day-why the hell did we have to kill Illidan? \r\nI mean, I understand that the purpose alot of raid content is to lend some closure to the story lines from WCIII (And WC I and II in the cases of say, Blackrock Spire or Zul'Aman), and Illidan was definitely a major character who remained something of a loose end after WCIII.\r\n(Unless Blizzard, dare I say it, leave a guy to die when he logically should. Yeah, yeah, I realize that the original plan was to have a higher quality cutscene and show that Illidan, while defeated, did survive-whatever. \"The bottom of Icecrown was merely a setback!\")\r\n\r\nBut, look at the other Raid Bosses and Villains we've faced so far-\r\n\r\nNefarian-Tried to create a new brood of dragons and loose them on the world and *!@# ^&*! up the way his father did.\r\n\r\nC'Thun-Was trying to conquer the world with ugly bug things.\r\n\r\nKel'Thuzad (the first time)-Was just kind of a ^&*!@#bag. But really, leader of the Scourge outside of Northrend.\r\n\r\nKael'Thas-Went out of his $%^&ing gourd, got drunk on whatever moonjuice they were piping to him in the Netherstorm, then decided it would be a great idea to steal a Naaru, corrupt him, and then, say, I dunno, summon the leader of the most destructive organization in the universe in a kiddy pool at his summer home.\r\n\r\nI know I left out alot of major antagonists, but still, the point is, they all got what they deserved.\r\n\r\nBut what did Illidan do that was so bad? \r\nHe actually did a lot more good than harm.\r\n\r\nIn WCIII, he defeated Tichondrius, and severely hampered the Legion's offensive effort on the world tree by cutting their reinforcements. Without that edge, Archimonde would have set up a treehouse in Nordrassil and started taking a *!@# on Azeroth.\r\nOk, fine. In Frozen Throne, though, he did much, much more. First off, he jarred loose the scourge's foothold outside Northrend and effectively freeing The Forsaken. If you remember, he started casting this giant spell to shatter Icecrown, and was about halfway through it when Malfurion (&*!@#$bag) stopped him. He didn't destroy Icecrown or the Lich King, but the storyline indicates that it's this spell that causes Ner'Zhul's influence to wane enough to make Arthas come down with epilepsy or whatever, and wake Sylvanas up enough to cooperate with the dreadlords enough to stage the coup that sent Arthas back to Northrend, leaving the Scourge's future in Lordaeron in Kel'Thuzad's (cough) very capable hands. Of course, she turns on the dreadlords, screwing over the Legion...again...and freeing the Forsaken enough to establish themselves as a legitimate force and self reliant people.\r\nNow, while all that was happening, he was off in Outland, teaching the Blood Elves not to gnaw off their own hands in magic withdrawn frenzies, and went and kicked the ass of a Pit Lord who had enslaved the Broken in the Black Temple, screwing over the Legion...again. (Man, those guys just can't catch a good break.)\r\n\r\nSo why are we @#$%ed at him?\r\n\r\nBecause Kael'Thas attacked Shattrath? \r\nI mean, maybe Kael was just feeling crazy and cracked out from all the siphoned energy from the manaforges and thought, \"Hey, let's go knock over Shattrath.\" I mean, he's not known for great ideas. (See summoning Kil'Jaeden in kiddy pool reference.)\r\nNot his fault.\r\n\r\nBecause the Broken are being abused?\r\nUh, I didn't see any Broken being beaten up or getting all Rodney King'd on when I strolled through BT. From what I'm to understand, the Ashtounge held a place of honor in the Illidari. And it's not like Illidan enslaved them and made them get all ugly. The Orcs, under the influence of the legion, !@#$ed up the Temple of Karabor originally, and Magtheridon was just housesitting for Kil'Jaeden until he got his credit in order so that he could refinance the Black Temple or something. They actually had it pretty good with Illidan compared to all the other !@#$ they went through. Guess the grass is always greener on the other side of...the Temple...\r\n\r\nBecause he's mean to Maiev?\r\nHonestly, who gives a ^&*! In TFT, Malfurion has the crazy %^&*! arrested for lying about Tyrande's fate. Whisperwind would have been left for dead so that Maiev would get her shot at Illidan. Technically, she's an enemy of the Night Elf government, and just generally a psycho hose-beast.\r\n\r\nBecause he's a staunch enemy of the Burning Legion and the Scourge?\r\nYeah! Off with his head! How dare he fight those guys?\r\nOh, wait...\r\n\r\nI mean, I know alot of people will disagree with me because of what happened with the Sundering and whatnot, and that Illidan was a loose cannon and had to be eliminated. But, I'm just putting it out there.", "date": "2009-06-28T12:41:55-05:00", "rating": 122, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I totally agree.   I think the reason everyone hates him is because he wouldn't take no for an answer from Tyrande, and people like Malfurion more? I don't know. I think Tyrande definitely has/had feelings for Illidan, otherwise she wouldn't have helped him escape.  I think Malfurion was too much a of a purest, and needed to give his brother a break, especially since Illidan sacrificed himself to save a lot of people, (and prove his love to Tyrande.)  There need to be more story on Illidan, and he needs to not be dead. He's one of the more compelling of all the characters in all of Warcraft lo", "creationdate": "2009-06-28T12:41:56-05:00", "id": 482016, "rating": 12, "commentid": 761315, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bardgal", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This comment is good and you should feel good.  I still wish they hadn't pulled Kael and Illidan's names out of the hat when they were trying to figure out who the villains of BC ought to be  and arbitrarily decided that both guys are nucking futs, but the fact that some people still dig Illidan and realize he's not the root of all that's evil, yo (but you can call him 'cookie' *warglaive'd*) makes me joyous.", "creationdate": "2011-07-12T23:48:33-05:00", "id": 252016, "rating": 8, "commentid": 761315, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I agree with this for the most part but why does no one remember that even though his intentions were good when he was casting that spell to kill the LK he was actually gambling with the world cause by the time he would have successfully killed arthas there was a good chance of the world blowing up according to whats said in TFT if i remember correctly.", "creationdate": "2011-08-23T18:41:03-05:00", "id": 260268, "rating": 3, "commentid": 761315, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "630023", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He would have melted the icecaps but not blown up the world.  Still not the greatest outcome.", "creationdate": "2011-10-28T20:01:09-05:00", "id": 273908, "rating": 4, "commentid": 761315, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I enjoy this post. Illidan's like, my favorite character in WoW lore, and he's always so misunderstood. Poor Illidan. Q~Q", "creationdate": "2014-07-26T04:09:38-05:00", "id": 760176, "rating": 5, "commentid": 761315, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Darasin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": fal