{"commentv2": 1, "number": 124, "id": 805286, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "PinkWolf", "body": "funny/sad fact:\r\nIn the dialogue between Malfurion and Remulos, it is believed(or proven) that [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22917]Illidan[/url] did indeed became insane...\r\n[i]\r\nMalfurion Stormrage says: Cenarius fights at my side. Illidan sits atop his throne in Outland \u2013 brooding. I'm afraid that the [u]loss to Arthas proved to be his breaking point[/u]. Madness has embraced him, Remulos. He replays the events in his mind a thousand times per day, [b][u]but in his mind, he is the victor and Arthas is utterly defeated.[/u] [/b]He is too far gone, old friend. I fear that the time may soon come that our bond is tested and it will not be as it was at the Well in Zin-Azshari.[/i]\r\n\r\nI personally feel sry for Illidan, he was(maybe still is) my fav Warcraft character.As for Arthas, i can't wait to see what blizz has in stored for us in Icecrown!\r\n[i]\r\n[small]Reply to Tolki's comment! ^_^[i][/i][/small][/i]", "date": "2009-08-09T16:07:09-05:00", "rating": 68, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 125, "id": 852701, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "342097", "body": "In my opinion, it's very stupid that Blizzard made epic characters from the Warcraft Universe daily raids.  Most of the Dragon Aspects, Kil'Jaeden, Illidan..\r\n\r\nIf they make the Lich King an easy daily raid I'm gonna start holding Blizzard employees hostage.", "date": "2009-09-26T18:09:29-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "First of all, weekly raids.  Second of all, they have to die some time don't they? The whole point of World of Warcraft is to resolve the unfinished storylines from Warcraft. This includes Illidan, Arthas, Medivh, Malygos, soon Deathwing, and many other story characters.  I'm glad they have a raid system like this, and aren't just killing off powerful lore characters in easy 5-mans (such as Azjol-Nerub, where you kill one of the most powerful lore characters, despite his ressurection later)", "creationdate": "2009-12-13T18:29:46-06:00", "id": 434390, "rating": 3, "commentid": 852701, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "258919", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
