{"commentv2": 1, "number": 175, "id": 1746263, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nobbel", "body": "Two video guides for the Black Temple:\r\nHow to Solo: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5NFEJ5JqFD8&hd=1&t=12m53s\r\nHow to 3-man: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qyetuXk_0VA&hd=1&t=7m1s\r\n\r\nEnjoy ^_^", "date": "2012-10-20T06:28:51-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 176, "id": 1771554, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tayas", "body": "Soloed tonight as 90 Fury Warrior ilvl485\r\nThe phase when he throws the blades down and summons the two elementals is tricky. Fight them next to a blade as they do more damage the further from their respective blades they are. The one that is furthest from his blade MUST be nuked down super fast or you will die. I saved all CDs for this and still very nearly died.\r\n\r\nNot too hard to solo though. I expect healing classes will have it much easier.", "date": "2012-11-29T19:15:10-06:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thanks for this comment, made everything a lot easier for me once I understood that phase. After I killed the far elemental it was all back to easy.", "creationdate": "2012-12-14T22:19:15-06:00", "id": 611860, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1771554, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Harraser", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 177, "id": 1774026, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Greyvax", "body": "This was easier than I expected as a 483 fury warrior.\r\n\r\nDid straight up normal DPS & 1 minute cooldowns on phase 1, and bandaged after he flew up.\r\n\r\nPhase 2 I popped all of my dps cooldowns and burned down the 2 elementals in the middle, ended this phase with just under half health.\r\n\r\nPhase 3 wasn't too difficult, as he is doing mostly melee.  Pop DBTS here and any dps cooldowns that are back up and second wind should take care of the rest if you get low.  Didn't even have to use a healing pot.", "date": "2012-12-02T14:29:22-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 178, "id": 1778425, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Berrenger", "body": "Solo'd as a Fury Warrior, Titan's Grip, ilvl 476, no buffs.\n\nMy strategy was a mix of those posted by Greyvax and Tavas. \n\nPhase 1, didn't use any cooldowns, just regular dps to 66% health.\n\nPhase 2, before the elementals spawned I bandaged up to full health. When the elementals spawned I stood right next to one blade but targeted the elemental that spawns from the other blade. Popped all cooldowns and nuked that elemental down as quickly as possible as he does much more damage the further away from his blade he is. The other elemental did negligible damage and was easily dealt with once the first was down.\n\nPhase 3, I was at about 20% health but Second Wind prevented me from going much lower. Tank and spank Illidan until Maiev shows up whilst avoiding blue flames on the floor. Once Maiev and Illidan finish their little chat, nuke him down.", "date": "2012-12-09T13:53:54-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thanks, was easy with 472 geared lock once I knew what to do on phase 2. Saved my embers this phase, popped havoc and gave them both a chaos bolt in the rear. Died once before I read this, but soulstone save me a run back. No glaive, but I got all my T6.", "creationdate": "2013-01-23T11:18:56-06:00", "id": 625639, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1778425, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Elvisi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-09T13:54:45-06:00", 1, "Berrenger"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 179, "id": 1788366, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "PanzersSkywall", "body": "Solo'd as 460 BM Hunter.\r\n\r\nFerocity pet, just normal DPS phase 1.\r\n\r\nAt 66% when he drops down the 2 glaives, that's where you want to pop every cooldown (stampede as well) to burn the 2 elementals down. That part is the only challenge.\r\n\r\nP3 resume AFK-autoshot, good luck on loot!", "date": "2012-12-27T20:37:31-06:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 180, "id": 1790998, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "mrmonkeyman", "body": "Solo'd as 460 ilvl Prot Warrior. Very Simple with Second Wind. Simply dps him through the first phase saving cooldowns for phase 2. Phase 2 do as others have mentioned, stand by one of the blades and kill the elemental from the farther blade first and avoid standing in fire. I bandaged up before phase 3 began but really it wasn't necessary as i was back down to 35% and second wind was keeping me up all the way to the end of the fight.", "date": "2013-01-02T03:24:30-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As a 474 Combat Rogue, this strat works as well. Save all your DPS and protection cooldowns for those Elementals - AR,KS,Evade,Cloak, etc -stand by one blade, burn the one that spawns by the other down first. Phase 1 and 3 are nothing that Leaching Poison/Shiv can't handle.", "creationdate": "2013-01-21T02:51:44-06:00", "id": 624891, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1790998, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "digitalutopia1", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 181, "id": 1803622, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kasa24", "body": "Just tried to solo this on my paladin, and got my butt handed to me first try. I didn't realize that the Flames of Azzinoth have to be tanked near the warglaives of azzinoth or else they enrage and do tremendous damage. If you tank both of them in between the warglaives, you shouldn't have a problem with them enraging.", "date": "2013-01-24T17:04:43-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "never knew this after killing him so many times, couldnt understand why i kept geting nuked whilst doin the run around warlock thing :D thanks for post", "creationdate": "2013-01-25T07:44:59-06:00", "id": 626273, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1803622, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Firlox", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 182, "id": 1804284, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1082862", "body": "Pretty much any class should be able to solo him at 90 in basic heroics-level (463) gear. You want to save your CDs for killing the elementals in phase 2, as they can hurt a LOT. Other than that, just demolish him. At 4 million health, most classes can probably down him in about a minute and a half.", "date": "2013-01-26T02:59:52-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 183, "id": 1810804, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "antibrian", "body": "After killing him, many [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=23498]Parasitic Shadowfeinds[/url] kept spawning and murdering me. What's the deal?", "date": "2013-02-08T13:14:43-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 184, "id": 1813317, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "voodoopimp", "body": "If you have decent DPS and/or self-healing, you can just stand in the fire while you kill the flames and not have to worry about accidentally pulling them too far.  The rest of the fight should be trivial for any class.", "date": "2013-02-13T19:27:11-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 185, "id": 1817517, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nekrotik", "body": "At level 90 with decent raid gear, there's only one thing to know about soloing this fight. In the second phase, stand in the middle of the circle to kill the fire elementals that spawn there. If you move them away, they'll enrage and quickly kill you. The fire coming out of the ground won't hurt much, and you'll easily burn them down to start the last phase. Fighting Illidan himself is easier than drowning a kitten (not that I would know).", "date": "2013-02-23T20:33:17-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This helped a lot, knowing I just had to stand in the middle of the circle to kill the fire elementals easily. Thank you!", "creationdate": "2013-04-25T18:39:37-05:00", "id": 653803, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1817517, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "crescentmoon2967", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-02-23T20:34:00-06:00", 1, "Nekrotik"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 186, "id": 1822146, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lodenghar", "body": "Solo'd at 90 as a SMF war, save cd's for flames phase and kill them asap rest is cake.", "date": "2013-03-06T01:59:14-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 187, "id": 1833180, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sharessa", "body": "90 Feral Druid with iLevel 480 (mix of Valor and heroic 5-man gear). Specced Renewal (use when necessary) and Dream of Cenarius (use with 5 combo point Predatory Swiftness procs for healing).\r\n\r\nThe only hard part about this fight is phase 2.  When a Flame of Azzinoth gets too far away from the blade that spawned it, it will increase its damage by 500%.  If you're soloing this gets to be problematic since you can't be by both blades at once.  The solution is to stay close to one of the blades while DPSing the Flame that spawned at the [i]other[/i] blade until it is dead.  Blow all cooldowns for this part of the fight and void standing in the fire if possible, too.  Once the far Flame is dead, kill the other one and phase 3 will begin.\r\n\r\nFor all the other phases, I just did my normal DPS rotation and healed when Predatory Swiftness procced.\r\n\r\nThe other fights that gave me problems in the Black Temple were [npc=22948] and [npc=23426].", "date": "2013-03-23T09:31:23-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The Note about the elementals and their buffs helped immensely... my brother and I were duoing this and wiped on phase 2 a few times before we saw this... after that we just split up in phase 2 and it was pretty easy.", "creationdate": "2013-04-21T03:29:40-05:00", "id": 652650, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1833180, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ejikazuma", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "awesome tip worked perfectly thanks very much.", "creationdate": "2013-04-28T15:18:39-05:00", "id": 654562, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1833180, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "irishbloke", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thank you Sharessa, your tip worked for me as well. 85 Demon Lock soloed except for Illidan I had to bring my 2nd account 85 druid tank in to help had him on the other Flame worked great. First time in BT only died 3 times :P /cheers", "creationdate": "2013-05-19T13:17:44-05:00", "id": 659760, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1833180, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TheMitigator", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
