{"commentv2": 1, "number": 189, "id": 1837104, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Holyraider", "body": "Fun fact: Bulwalk of Azzinoth was actually the CHEST of a demon called Azzinoth", "date": "2013-03-31T09:26:56-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 190, "id": 1837958, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Elfgar", "body": "Soloed Illidan today as ret pally ilvl 500. He killed me on first attempt which was my only death in BT on first solo run (I was surprised). The reason he killed me was I wasted too much effort before he threw the glaives and I didn't have enough peak DPS to quickly kill the elementals that emerge in phase two. On my second attempt I saved my CDs to burn down those green elementals. Then in phase three I waited until the last possible moment to use my Lay on Hands to heal myself to 100%. After that I just avoided the blue stuff on the ground and burned him up... the end was kind of sad for me because BT is now so easy.", "date": "2013-04-02T07:07:34-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-04-02T07:08:17-05:00", 1, "Elfgar"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 191, "id": 1845986, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "anasa", "body": "Soloed on a 90 WW Monk in ilvl ~480. \r\n\r\nSaved both Touch of Karma and Diffuse Magic for the glaive elemental phase. Tore them down easily and the rest was cake.", "date": "2013-04-22T17:14:27-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 192, "id": 1846116, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "968833", "body": "Absolutely no problem for a combat rogue\r\n\r\njust remember to save your cds for the flames and For the love of god stay in the middle if you move out of the middle the adds will cream you if you stay in the middle the flames do nothing", "date": "2013-04-23T03:15:51-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 193, "id": 1848572, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Aeolynn", "body": "Just a tip for the ones soloing this one: there is a huge chance that phase 2 will still kill you as a 90, if you stay near one of the Warglaives and just dps the Elementals. You should stay in the very middle of the circle for some easy time.", "date": "2013-04-30T08:51:58-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 194, "id": 1853559, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "talenlee", "body": "For those of us soloing the Black Temple who aren't old hands at it, in a post-Pandaria world:\r\n[ul][li]When you head up the stairs, turn [b]left[/b], not right. It'll put you closer to Akama to start the encounter.[/li]\r\n[li]When he throws down the Blades of Azzinoth, you want to keep the fire elementals [b]NEAR[/b] their blades, not [b]AWAY[/b] from their blades. I can't find any mention of this anywhere - if you pull them away from the blades, they will go rather nuts and kill you to death. Sticking in the circle should be plenty close enough.[/li]\r\n[li]There is no 'demon' phase, nor any need to do any malarkey with traps. At around 20% health, Illidan will drop to his knees and start a speech. [b]Burn him here.[/b] Maiev will appear, she'll get stroppy with him, and rather than getting into the traps-and-triggers stuff, you can just pound on him. He'll drop pretty easily.[/li][/ul]\r\nThose are the only real changes I can find in this encounter from the historical comments presented here.", "date": "2013-05-16T11:26:23-05:00", "rating": 50, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yeah, you really need to be careful with those blades. I'm pretty sure I did it wrong, I was fighting both elementals near the east blade and the damage was *insane*. I killed them tho but it was a little scary. Probably best like you said to fight them in the middle.", "creationdate": "2014-03-03T16:52:32-06:00", "id": 732651, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1853559, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "huldu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "When soloing, even better than standing near the blades is standing on the grate between them. If you fight there, the elements DO NOT enrage, and the phase is much, much easier.", "creationdate": "2014-06-07T23:24:51-05:00", "id": 750149, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1853559, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nahkhaz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 195, "id": 1865936, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1128392", "body": "462 Ret Pally.  Was a very easy solo.  He was down without much problem.  On elementals keep in the circle and dps them down quick.  After that it is a tank and spank with no major issues to worry about.\r\n\r\nGood luck!\r\n\r\nGriswold\r\nAlliance Mannaroth", "date": "2013-06-12T22:05:57-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 196, "id": 1866277, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "direpath", "body": "Note to soloers, as this was revealed to me by a guildie...\r\n\r\nI had not killed him solo as I had little to seek from him except reputation. I had a heck of a time versus the Flames as they could crisp me even in T13.\r\n\r\nTheir damage is greater further from their respective glaive. So...\r\n\r\nStand next to a glaive. Burn the furthest one first and the second one will be simple.", "date": "2013-06-13T15:56:37-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 197, "id": 1869307, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "319936", "body": "Hearthstone: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/hearthstone/card=556&image&notip]Illidan Stormrage[/url]. his weapon: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/hearthstone/card=1639&image&notip]Warglaive of Azzinoth[/url], [url=http://www.wowhead.com/hearthstone/card=1642&image&notip]Dual Warglaives[/url]\r\n\r\nhis brother: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/hearthstone/card=274&image&notip]Malfurion Stormrage[/url]", "date": "2013-06-22T02:59:03-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 198, "id": 1873075, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ClearlyConfused", "body": "Before I start I'd like to tell anyone that is looking, [b]You [u]CANNOT[/u], I repeat, [u]CANNOT[/u] skip to Illidan; you must still kill all other bosses before the concubine chamber opens.[/b]\n\nI solo'ed Illidan as a iLvl 503 Guardian druid.\n\nThe fight was pretty straight forward: attack, move, loot. The only thing that may screw you is [i][b]Phase 2[/b][/i] when he throws his glaives. As others have mentioned, the further away an Elemental is to its glaive the more damage it does (and it can get ugly fast) so pop your O-%^&*s (CD's) on which ever one you choose then move the other to its original glaive; unless you have good spell awareness, then just heal though the damage. After that its back to a regular tank-and-spank fight.", "date": "2013-07-03T00:55:36-05:00", "rating": 26, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-07-03T00:56:10-05:00", 1, "ClearlyConfused"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 199, "id": 1877666, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Morbius", "body": "Soloed this with my 85 blood DK in 417 ilevel gear including Jade Forest greens and auction house blues.\r\n\r\nThis fight happens in three phases. In the first phase you fight Illidan. Then he flies up and throws down his warglaives and two elementals spawn. After you kill them Illidan lands and you fight him.\r\n\r\nIn the second phase fight the two elementals in the middle of the grate because the damage they do increases the further away they are from their warglaive. By fighting them in the middle you keep their damage low. They also lay down an AE that you should avoid.\r\n\r\nAfter the elementals are dead Illidan will land and you can finish him off. He puts a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40932]DOT[/url] on you that didn't seem to do much damage to me.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHere's the video:\r\nhttp://youtu.be/65zBcR58GpE", "date": "2013-07-16T21:27:30-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 200, "id": 1878483, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1133292", "body": "[url=http://youtu.be/88NxsNWykQk]Lvl 90 Warrior Soloing Illidan Stormrage[/url]\r\n\r\nHappy farming.", "date": "2013-07-19T06:10:15-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
