{"commentv2": 1, "number": 237, "id": 2556865, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Maravec", "body": "So, I just finished soloing Black Temple.\n\nI read through a few comments that stated there are some issues with initiating the fight with Illidan, as well as ending the fight. What I found was that reaching the point where Akama tells you Illidan is meditating in the courtyard and then running toward Illidan should cause him to turn his head and address Akama. As for ending the fight, there's a tendency for some NPCs to have the \"I would've gotten away with it, too\" dialog, and I've noticed some NPCs won't die until they've gotten in the last word. Such is the case with Illidan, after which it was necessary for me to whack him once more. Wait until it falls quiet, then smack him. That did the trick, and let me loot his corpse.", "date": "2018-03-08T21:01:34-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2018-03-08T21:02:34-06:00", 1, "Maravec"]}
