{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 424570, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "227475", "body": "I wouldent be surprised if illidan came in outta know where when you fight the lich king", "date": "2008-10-29T16:42:28-05:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I betcha Illidan never even died. Seems like he really is an indestructible machine, since this is the second time now that we thought he was dead, but yet manages to come up again. Kael'thas pulled the same stunt, I wouldn't be surprised if Vashj is still alive too.  If they bothered to have Illidan in WotLK, I'm thinking a) You will be fighting alongside an army of NPCs to finally damn the Lich King to hell. I'd like to see that happen, because so far, it's like 25 footmen killing Illidan in Warcraft, instead of a named person. In WoWWiki Lore it will be: Illidan was alive for 10,541 years, ", "creationdate": "2008-10-29T16:42:29-05:00", "id": 357666, "rating": 26, "commentid": 424570, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Groobert6456", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "actually, in lore Illidan was killed by Maiev+25 red-shirt footmen/grunts.  almost every boss has a famous NPC there to steal all the credits for the kill.  in Kil'jaeden it was that girl and kalecgos, and in malygos it was the red dragonflight, on yoggsaron it was the 4 keepers and so on.  I bet u that we're the ones who are gonna work like hell to kill the lich king on icecrown citadel, and yet Tirion is the one who's gonna get all the credits, since I bet he's gonna be a part of the encounter, and if he's there and survives, then on lore he's the one who killed arthas, \"with some help from ", "creationdate": "2008-10-29T16:42:29-05:00", "id": 426513, "rating": 7, "commentid": 424570, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 264, "username": "Rankkor", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ugh, stop voting this up, Illidan isn't alive again.  This Illidan is just part of a quest [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=13361]The Hunter and the Prince[/url] where you look at Arthas's Past to see just how much of a badass Arthas was.  People really need to understand that just like in every other RPG, we, the players, are Heroes.  We aren't the peons, or the grunts, or the sergeants, or the lieutenants, though we certainly do work our way up through the ranks.  The lore for Illidan will read along the lines of: With the aid of Akama, leader of the Broken and the Heroes of Azeroth (that'", "creationdate": "2008-10-29T16:42:29-05:00", "id": 405482, "rating": 6, "commentid": 424570, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "272760", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well in wow you are spost to be a hero like Wisperwind and thrall just not known or in any lore whatsoever but 25 thralls vs one lvl 83 elete i think thats more along the lines of what blizzard was planing Were not footmen....were footmen with awsome gear and special pointy sticks", "creationdate": "2008-11-07T14:30:57-06:00", "id": 54889, "rating": 11, "commentid": 424570, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Shoningun", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=13400 And what an awesome quest it was.", "creationdate": "2008-12-16T06:42:56-06:00", "id": 65172, "rating": 8, "commentid": 424570, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Groobert6456", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "