{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 1134634, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MalygosHelper", "body": "[quote]When Arthas fought Illidan, Illidan was at his full strength, yet this was before Arthas put on the Lich King's helm, which means that Arthas was not at his full power. This just goes to show how much of a badass Arthas is going to be now.[/quote]\r\n\r\nLoads of many wrong things here actually.\r\n\r\n1) You cannot know Illidan was at his full power, also, he never used his powerful demon form, nor any magical attacks. Magic is Illidan speciality, Arthas is good in using blades, expecially a legendary sword, Frostmourne.\r\n2) Arthas was at his full power, the Lich King restored him his powers. And he was wielding a legendary weapon, thing that Illidan doesn't had. If you're talking about Lich King and not Arthas (as Arthas died that day), then it's completely different: The Lich King has just the body of Arthas, but the spirit of Ner'zhul.\r\n3) Arthas, as one being, is less powerful than Illidan. On the other hand, Arthas is a better warrior.\r\n\r\nIn the cinematic, aswell as in the quest, it's said that Arthas was near his death, after the duel... You can imagine the consequences.\r\nAlso, i'm wondering that, as, since the end of the campaign, Illidan declared war against the Burning Legion, the Scourge and the Illidari, in an other reality, could have been allied. That would have been quite interesting.", "date": "2010-10-04T13:06:32-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
